  {category:"Appointments",items:[
    {q:"How do I create a new appointment?",a:'Click "New Appointment" in the sidebar or the button in the top right of the dashboard. Fill in the customer name, company (optional), phone, email, and job address. Select the service type (HVAC or Plumbing), technician, date, time, and any notes. Click Save to add it to the schedule.'},
    {q:"How do I search for appointments?",a:'The search bar supports plain text and smart keyword filters.\n\nPLAIN TEXT\nType any name, company, phone number, address, technician, service type, or invoice number — matching jobs appear instantly.\n\nDATE FILTERS\ntoday · tomorrow · this week · next week · this month · overdue\n\nSTATUS FILTERS\nscheduled · completed · cancelled · in progress · on the way\nPartial words work too — \"sched\" matches \"scheduled\".\n\nSERVICE TYPE\nplumbing · hvac · maintenance\n\nINVOICE FILTERS\nunpaid · outstanding · paid · invoice sent · no invoice\n\nCOMBINING KEYWORDS\nYou can mix a name with any filter:\n\"Randy plumbing\" — Randy\'s plumbing jobs\n\"Glenn scheduled\" — Glenn\'s scheduled jobs\n\"unpaid hvac\" — unpaid HVAC jobs\n\"completed this month\" — jobs completed this month'},
    {q:"How do I edit an appointment?",a:'Click any appointment card on the dashboard or calendar to open it. Then click the Edit (pencil) icon in the top right of the detail panel. Make your changes and click Save.'},
    {q:"How do I reschedule an appointment?",a:'You can drag and drop an appointment card on the Month calendar view to a new date. Or open the appointment, click Edit, and change the date and time fields manually. Both methods save automatically.'},
    {q:"How do I cancel an appointment?",a:'Open the appointment and click Edit, then change the status to Cancelled. The appointment stays in the system for record-keeping but is removed from the active schedule.'},
    {q:"How do I delete an appointment?",a:'Open the appointment and click the Delete button. Deleted appointments are soft-deleted and can be recovered from the Deleted Jobs page under Admin Tools for as long as the retention period allows.'},
    {q:"How do I send a notification to a customer?",a:'Open the appointment and click the Notify Customer button. This sends an SMS to the customer\'s phone with the appointment details and technician name.'},
    {q:"How do I mark an appointment as complete?",a:'Open the appointment and change the status to Completed, or have the technician mark it complete in the Field Tech app. Completed jobs move to the Completed Jobs list and become eligible for invoicing.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Recurring Appointments",items:[
    {q:"How do I set up a recurring appointment?",a:'When creating or editing an appointment, check the "Recurring" toggle. Select the frequency (weekly, monthly, annually) and an optional end date. Save the parent appointment, then use the Generate Recurring button to create all future instances.'},
    {q:"How do I edit just one instance of a recurring appointment?",a:'Open the specific instance on the calendar or dashboard and click Edit. Choose "Edit this appointment only" when prompted. Your changes apply only to that single occurrence.'},
    {q:"How do I edit all future recurring appointments at once?",a:'Open any instance in the series and click Edit. Choose "Edit this and all future appointments" to apply changes to every upcoming occurrence in the series.'},
    {q:"How do I reschedule one recurring event on the calendar?",a:'Drag the specific instance on the Month view to a new date. Only that instance moves - the rest of the series stays on its original schedule.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Customers",items:[
    {q:"Where do I find the Customers list?",a:'Click "Customers" in the left sidebar. You will see a searchable list of all customers imported or created from appointments. You can filter by name, company, phone, email, or address using the search bar at the top of the page.'},
    {q:"How do I edit a customer\'s information?",a:'Go to the Customers page, find the customer, and click the Edit button on their row. A dialog will open where you can update their name, company, phone, email, billing address, and CC email recipients. Saving the edit automatically updates all linked appointments too.'},
    {q:"How do I add CC email recipients to a customer?",a:'Open the customer edit dialog and scroll to the "Additional Email Recipients" section. Type an email address and press Enter or comma to add it. These addresses are pre-filled when sending estimates or invoices to that customer.'},
    {q:"How are customers created?",a:'Customers are created automatically when you create a new appointment - the system uses the phone number as the unique identifier. You can also manually add a new contact using the New Contact button on the Customers page, or bulk import via CSV.'},
    {q:"How does the job history work for a customer?",a:'Click the History button on any customer row to open the History drawer. It shows a full lifetime summary: total jobs, total invoiced, pending estimates, outstanding balance, and a color-coded list of every job with service type, technician notes, and period totals.'},
    {q:"How do I import customers from a CSV?",a:'Click the Import button on the Customers page. Download the template if needed, fill in your customer data, and upload the file. The system maps columns automatically and skips duplicates by phone number.'},
    {q:"Why does the customer record show a job count instead of a service type badge?",a:'The app was updated so that service type is tied to the individual job, not the customer. A customer can have both HVAC and Plumbing jobs over time. The badge now shows their total job count instead.'},
    {q:"How do service locations work?",a:'In the customer edit dialog, you can add multiple service locations - the actual addresses where work is performed. These are separate from the billing address and useful when a customer has multiple properties.'},
    {q:"Are customers synced to QuickBooks?",a:'Only Plumbing customers are synced to QuickBooks. HVAC customers are never saved to QB - estimates and invoices for HVAC jobs are handled locally via Gmail only. This is a business rule that cannot be changed from the app.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Invoicing & Payments",items:[
    {q:"How do I send an invoice after a job is completed?",a:'Open the completed appointment and click "Ready to Invoice". Create or confirm the line items in the estimate panel, then click Send. Plumbing jobs send to QuickBooks and email. HVAC jobs send via Gmail only and are never saved to QB.'},
    {q:"How do I mark a job as paid in full?",a:'Open the appointment and click "Mark Paid" in the invoice section. This updates the invoice status to Paid and moves the job to the invoiced/paid category.'},
    {q:"What if a customer pays in advance before the job is done?",a:'You can create a partial payment or mark the estimate as paid early. Use the payment field in the invoice dialog to enter the amount received. The balance will update automatically.'},
    {q:"Where do invoiced jobs go after they\'re invoiced?",a:'Invoiced jobs appear in the Completed Jobs list with an invoice badge. They are also visible in the customer\'s History drawer under their full job history.'},
    {q:"How do I find a past invoice?",a:'Go to the Customers page, find the customer, and click History. All past invoices are listed there with amounts and statuses. You can also search for a job by invoice number in the main search bar.'},
    {q:"What is the difference between HVAC and Plumbing invoicing?",a:'Plumbing jobs create QuickBooks invoices and sync customer data to QB. HVAC jobs use local invoices sent via Gmail only and are never created in or synced to QuickBooks. This rule applies to every invoice and estimate in the system.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Reports",items:[
    {q:"Where do I find the Reports page?",a:'Click "Admin Tools" in the left sidebar to expand the admin section, then click "Reports". It is visible to admin, dispatcher, and both roles.'},
    {q:"What does the Reports Overview show?",a:'The Overview tab shows five key metrics: Total Revenue (all invoiced jobs), Total Jobs, Completed Jobs, Outstanding Balance (unpaid invoices), Pending Estimates value, and the count of active Recurring Series.'},
    {q:"How do I filter reports by date range?",a:'At the top of the Reports page there is a date range bar. Click "This Month", "Last 90 Days", "This Year", or "Custom". For Custom, two date pickers appear - set a from and to date and click Apply. All tabs update automatically with the filtered data.'},
    {q:"What is the Revenue by Month tab?",a:'Shows a horizontal bar chart of invoiced revenue by calendar month, most recent first, for the selected date range. Each bar shows the month label and dollar amount.'},
    {q:"What is the By Service Type tab?",a:'Shows total revenue and job count broken out by service type (HVAC, Plumbing, etc.) for the selected period, sorted highest revenue first.'},
    {q:"What is the By Technician tab?",a:'Shows total revenue and job count per technician for the selected period, sorted highest revenue first.'},
    {q:"What is the Top Customers tab?",a:'Lists the top 10 customers by total revenue for the selected period, ranked with their job count and phone number.'},
    {q:"What is the Outstanding tab?",a:'Shows all customers with unpaid invoices in the selected period, with their total outstanding balance and number of unpaid jobs. The total is displayed prominently at the top.'},
    {q:"What is the Recurring Jobs tab?",a:'Shows stats that are always unfiltered regardless of your date range selection: total active recurring series, total generated instances, a breakdown by frequency (annual, monthly, etc.), and a list of customers who have recurring jobs.'},
    {q:"How do I export report data?",a:'Click the "Export CSV" button in the top right of the Reports page. It downloads a CSV file with all sections: overview totals, revenue by month, by service type, by technician, top customers, outstanding balances, and recurring job counts. The selected date range is included in the file header.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Technicians",items:[
    {q:"How do I add a technician?",a:'Go to the Technicians page from the sidebar. Click "Add Technician", fill in the name, phone, and service type (HVAC or Plumbing), and save. They will immediately appear in the technician dropdown when creating appointments.'},
    {q:"How do I remove or deactivate a technician?",a:'Go to the Technicians page and click the delete icon next to the technician. They will be removed from future assignment dropdowns but their historical appointments are preserved.'},
    {q:"How do I assign a technician to a job?",a:'When creating or editing an appointment, select the technician from the dropdown. Only technicians matching the job\'s service type are shown.'},
    {q:"Why can\'t I assign an HVAC technician to a Plumbing job?",a:'Technicians are assigned a service type (HVAC or Plumbing) when created. The dropdown filters to only show technicians whose service type matches the appointment\'s service type, preventing accidental misassignment.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Calendar",items:[
    {q:"How do I navigate the calendar?",a:'Use the arrow buttons at the top of the calendar to move forward or backward by month. Click "Today" to jump back to the current month. Click any day number to jump to the day view for that date.'},
    {q:"How do I see all appointments on a specific day?",a:'Click the number on any calendar day to open the day view, which lists all appointments scheduled for that date with their times, technicians, and statuses.'},
    {q:"How do I drag and drop to reschedule?",a:'On the Month calendar view, press and hold an appointment card, then drag it to a new date and release. The appointment is saved to the new date automatically. A single tap still opens the appointment detail.'},
    {q:"How do I switch between calendar and list view?",a:'Use the view toggle buttons in the top right of the dashboard to switch between Month calendar, Day view, and List view.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Dashboard & Navigation",items:[
    {q:"What do the stat cards at the top mean?",a:'Today shows appointments scheduled for today. Scheduled is the count of all upcoming non-cancelled appointments. Ready to Invoice shows completed jobs waiting to be invoiced. Cancelled shows cancelled appointments this period.'},
    {q:"How do I refresh the dashboard?",a:'The dashboard auto-refreshes every 15 seconds. To force a manual refresh, use the refresh button in the top right of the appointment list, or reload the page.'},
    {q:"How do I export all appointments to Excel?",a:'On the Customers page, click the Export button to download a CSV of all customers. On the Reports page, click Export CSV for revenue data. Individual appointment data can be exported from the search results.'},
    {q:"How do I switch between dark and light mode?",a:'Click "Light Mode" or "Dark Mode" at the bottom of the left sidebar to toggle. Your preference is saved for the session.'},
    {q:"Who can see the Admin Tools section?",a:'The Admin Tools section (Reports, Settings, Users, Audit Log, Deleted Jobs) is visible to users with the Admin, Dispatcher, or Both roles. Technician-only users do not see this section.'},
    {q:"What is the Audit Log?",a:'The Audit Log under Admin Tools records every change made in the system - who created, edited, or deleted an appointment, when it happened, and what changed. Useful for tracking down unexpected changes.'},
    {q:"What is the Deleted Jobs page?",a:'Found under Admin Tools, this page lists all soft-deleted appointments within the retention window. You can restore any deleted job back to active status from here.'}
  ]},
  {category:"Field Tech App",items:[
    {q:"How does the field tech app work?",a:'The Field Tech app is a separate PWA (installable on iPhone or Android) that technicians use in the field. It shows only the appointments assigned to them, lets them update status, add tech notes, and upload job photos.'},
    {q:"How does a technician mark a job complete in the field?",a:'In the Field Tech app, open the appointment and tap the status button to change it to "Completed". They can also add tech notes and photos before or after marking complete.'},
    {q:"How do I get notified when a job is completed?",a:'Enable push notifications in the scheduler dashboard. When a technician marks a job complete in the field app, a push notification is sent to subscribed dispatchers and admins.'},
    {q:"How do I install the Field Tech app on an iPhone?",a:'Open the Field Tech app URL in Safari on the iPhone. Tap the Share button (box with arrow), then tap "Add to Home Screen". The app installs as a PWA and behaves like a native app with Face ID login support.'},
